{
  "texts": [
    "SSL is a specific type of transfer learning where a feature extractor leverages large amounts of unlabeled data from the source domain.",
    "Here, the challenge is finding the pretext task the model should use to learn a reliable representation from unlabeled data only.",
    "There have been several proposals of pretext tasks for SSL [20].",
    "Selecting the most suitable one requires careful consideration of the characteristics and structures of the input data.",
    "The most common categories of SSL approaches are generative, contrastive, and predictive."
  ]
}